<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2015/06/nuspec.xsd">
  <metadata>
    <id>missive</id>
    <version>11.12.4</version>
    <title>Missive</title>
    <authors>Missive</authors>
    <owners>Graphixa</owners>
    <summary>Team email and chat from Missive. This package installs Missive using the official Windows installer downloaded from Missive at install time.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
[Missive](https://missiveapp.com) is team email and chat for productive teams—the application, name, and branding are from **Missive** (see [Terms](https://missiveapp.com/terms)).

## This Chocolatey package

- Downloads the Windows installer at install time from Missive’s official URL (`https://mail.missiveapp.com/download/win`); the package does **not** redistribute Missive binaries.
- Installs to `%SystemDrive%\Missive` (typically `C:\Missive` when the system drive is `C:`) using Missive’s silent installer switches.
- Creates all-users Start Menu and Public Desktop shortcuts to `Missive.exe` under that folder.

## Notes

- This is a **community-maintained** Chocolatey package. It is not published by Missive unless they choose to adopt it. If Missive requests changes or removal, the package maintainer will cooperate.
- Package source: [missive-chocolatey on GitHub](https://github.com/Graphixa/missive-chocolatey).
]]></description>
    <copyright>Copyright Missive</copyright>
    <projectUrl>https://missiveapp.com</projectUrl>
    <packageSourceUrl>https://github.com/Graphixa/missive-chocolatey</packageSourceUrl>
    <docsUrl>https://missiveapp.com/help</docsUrl>
    <licenseUrl>https://missiveapp.com/terms</licenseUrl>
    <tags>missive email collaboration team-chat community</tags>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <releaseNotes>https://missiveapp.com/changelog</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
